start up k3s cluster with: 
sudo systemctl start k3s

default kubeconfig found here:
sudo cp /etc/rancher/k3s/k3s.yaml ~/.kube/config

test and get node name with:
kubectl get nodes

Following needed to set label on the node so that some pods will load on it
kubectl label nodes NODE-NAME node-role.kubernetes.io/worker=
kubectl label nodes NODE-NAME node-role.kubernetes.io/database=

Start up argocd:
kubectl create -k ~/reclaim-the-stack/platform/argocd

I dont' think the following is needed any more as we removed linkerd:
kubectl label namespace default pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce=privileged
kubectl label namespace default pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn=privileged

Set up applications:
kubectl create -f argocd-root.yaml

argo password:
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o yaml | yq '.data.password | @base64d'
kubectl port-forward services/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443

I dont' think the following is needed any more as we removed linkerd:
Some changes: I had to remove the linkerd crds and instead run:
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/gateway-api/releases/download/v1.0.0/standard-install.yaml

